Not a good lecturer.  He uses overhead slides and doesn't label his graphs, making them useless when studying.  His exams are short answer and difficult compared to what he covers.  I loved Econ 103 when I took it elsewhere, but I was very disappointed with this class.
Great teacher that actually teaches econ and how it is used in the real world. Doesnt just put notes on a board rather has interesting lectures. He is tough but it's a good class and challenges you.

Gottheil's 102 is the reason I became an Econ major. He is an outstanding teacher for those who want more than just a blow off class. He doesn't rehash what is in the book. He expects you to read it on your own. And know it. He is EXTREMELY approachable. Use his office hours. Use him well.
he was really hard and didn't explain anything. i recommend you don't take this class, its hard and you don't learn anything.
Difficult to learn with all this stories

I was really more than a little disappointed after  having been taught by Gotheil for one semester... His style of teaching, his couldn't care less attitude ,and simply the way he designed this class, to say the least, leave a lot to be desired...

True that you could rote learn the book and pull out a C but I like to think that classes in college,even if they are not intellectually stimulating,should at least help you learn something.Gotheil,unfortunately,exemplifies tenure track gone mad. Pity that may be just 1/5 of students actually attended. Not even many of the TAs came after a while.

Read the textbook, go to his lecture, and you will be fine.  He is a good professor, and he's exams aren't difficult at all.  Prof. Gottheil's econ 102 was one of the easiest course that I have taken last semester.

The class consist of 1 midterm, 1 final, 5 pop quizzes(which in the end mean nothing), and hmwk. The hmwk is hard and deals with things that are not on the test nor is gone over in class. The exams are super hard so start studying like 2 weeks before. THIS CLASS IS NOT AT ALL EASY no matter what kind of student u r! Avoid if possible!
Please go to class and read your book! It's the only way you will pass!!
